Flutter Weather Dashboard - Pencil Design Proposals
File: fw-dashboard-new.pen
Canvas: mobile dashboard, 390 x 844
Goal: redesign the Home/Dashboard page so hourly weather exposes more than temperature:
wind, precipitation, humidity, and room for UV/sun data without making the screen feel crowded.

Current app context
- Existing weather data supports: temperature, feels like, humidity, wind speed/direction,
  UV index, sunrise, sunset, chance of precipitation, hourly forecast, daily forecast.
- Current visual language: dark weather surface, glass panels, cyan accent icons, bottom nav.
- Existing l10n labels include: Key conditions, Next hours, Wind Speed, Humidity,
  Chance of Rain, UV Index, Sunrise, Sunset.

Shared visual tokens
- Background: #071327 base, subtle depth toward #0D1E30.
- Primary glass: #0D1E30 at 72% opacity, blur 20, border #7FA5C8 at 20%.
- Secondary glass: #13263A at 20% opacity, border #7FA5C8 at 20%.
- Accent: #7CC4FF for selected states, icons, dividers, trend points.
- Primary text: #FFFFFF. Secondary text: #C4D5E4. Muted text: #9FB4C8.
- Main radius: 28-32 for hero/sheet panels, 14-20 for metric tiles.
- Icons: Lucide line icons, 16-24px.
- Spacing: 20px screen gutters, 12px grid gaps, 16-20px panel padding.

Hourly detail data model direction
- Extend HourlyForecast UI data to display:
  time, weather icon, temperature, wind speed, precipitation chance, humidity.
- Optional later: wind direction, UV, pressure, visibility, dew point.
- Keep the first release focused on hourly wind, precipitation, and humidity.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESIGN 1 - "Hourly Detail Rail"
Best when the top-level dashboard should stay familiar but each hourly card becomes more useful.

Pencil sketch

  .------------------------------------------------.
  | Sarajevo                              (search) |
  | Cloudy today                                   |
  |                                                |
  | .--------------------------------------------. |
  | | (sun)  23 C                    Feels 24 C  | |
  | |        Low rain risk      Wind 18.0 km/h   | |
  | '--------------------------------------------' |
  |                                                |
  | .---------------- key conditions ------------. |
  | | .----------. .----------. .----------.     | |
  | | | Rain 10% | | Wind 18 | | Humid 56%|     | |
  | | '----------' '----------' '----------'     | |
  | | .----------. .----------. .----------.     | |
  | | | UV 5.2   | | Rise 06 | | Set 19   |     | |
  | | '----------' '----------' '----------'     | |
  | '--------------------------------------------' |
  |                                                |
  | Next hours                         temp/wind   |
  | .--------. .--------. .--------. .--------.    |
  | | 13:00  | | 14:00  | | 15:00  | | 16:00  |    |
  | |  sun   | | cloud  | | rain   | | cloud  |    |
  | | 23 C   | | 24 C   | | 22 C   | | 21 C   |    |
  | | wind 8 | | wind 9 | | wind 12| | wind 11|    |
  | | rain 5 | | rain 8 | | rain 42| | rain 20|    |
  | | hum 56 | | hum 58 | | hum 65 | | hum 67 |    |
  | '--------' '--------' '--------' '--------'    |
  |                                                |
  | 7-day forecast                                 |
  | Today     sun            24 C / 15 C           |
  | Tue       cloud          21 C / 13 C           |
  |                                                |
  | HOME        MAP        ALERTS      Settings    |
  '------------------------------------------------'

Layout notes
- Keep the current dashboard hierarchy: top location, hero weather, key conditions,
  hourly forecast, daily forecast.
- Replace the compact hourly 70px cards with wider detail cards, about 112-124px wide.
- Each hourly card has one primary value and three mini rows:
  temperature, wind, precipitation, humidity.
- Use short labels inside the hourly card: Wind, Rain, Humid.
- Horizontal scroll is still the interaction, so the dashboard remains simple.
- This option is the lowest-risk implementation because the page structure barely changes.

Interaction notes
- Tap an hourly detail card to open a bottom sheet with the full hour:
  temperature, feels like, wind speed/direction, precipitation, humidity, UV if available.
- A small segmented control above the rail can switch emphasis:
  [All] [Temp] [Wind] [Rain] [Humidity].
- Default view is All.

Implementation direction
- Extend HourlyForecast to carry pop, humidity, windSpeed, and optionally windDirection.
- Update WeatherData.fromJson to parse those fields from each hourly item.
- Replace _HourlyStrip card content with the richer mini rows.
- Keep _InsightGrid as-is, but make it three columns on wider dashboard widths.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESIGN 2 - "Metric Lanes"
Best when the user wants to compare hourly temperature, wind, precipitation, and humidity quickly.

Pencil sketch

  .------------------------------------------------.
  | Sarajevo                              (locate) |
  | Updated 13:04                                  |
  |                                                |
  |       23 C                                     |
  |       Mostly sunny                             |
  |                                                |
  | .---------------- dashboard sheet -----------. |
  | | Key conditions                             | |
  | | [Rain 10%] [Wind 18 km/h] [Humidity 56%]  | |
  | | [UV 5.2]   [Sunrise 06:15] [Sunset 19:45] | |
  | |                                            | |
  | | Hourly detail                              | |
  | |       Now   14    15    16    17    18    | |
  | | Temp  23    24    24    21    20    19    | |
  | | Wind   8     9    12    11    10     7    | |
  | | Rain   5     8    42    20    14    10    | |
  | | Hum   56    58    65    67    70    72    | |
  | |                                            | |
  | | Daily forecast                             | |
  | | Today    sun              24 C / 15 C      | |
  | | Tue      cloud            21 C / 13 C      | |
  | '--------------------------------------------' |
  |                                                |
  | HOME        MAP        ALERTS      Settings    |
  '------------------------------------------------'

Layout notes
- The hourly section becomes a compact matrix instead of a row of cards.
- Columns are hours. Rows are weather measures:
  Temp, Wind, Rain, Humidity.
- Freeze metric labels on the left and horizontally scroll the hour columns.
- This is the densest way to show multi-hour, multi-metric weather without stacking cards.
- Use icon labels on the left when possible:
  thermometer, wind, cloud-rain, droplets.
- Highlight the highest precipitation hour with cyan text or a subtle filled cell.

Interaction notes
- Horizontal scroll on the hourly matrix.
- Tap a row label to emphasize that metric across all hours.
- Tap a column/hour to select it; selected column gets a soft cyan border.
- Selected hour updates a small "Focused hour" row above or below the matrix:
  "15:00: 24 C, wind 12 km/h, rain 42%, humidity 65%".

Implementation direction
- Create a new HourlyMetricTable widget.
- Use a horizontal SingleChildScrollView with fixed-width columns.
- Keep the left label column outside the horizontal scroll so labels remain readable.
- This design needs careful responsive sizing, but it scales best for comparison.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESIGN 3 - "Forecast Tabs"
Best when the dashboard should expose many hourly metrics without showing all of them at once.

Pencil sketch

  .------------------------------------------------.
  | .--------------------------------------------. |
  | | Sarajevo                         (pin)     | |
  | | Mostly sunny today                         | |
  | |                                            | |
  | | 23 C                         Feels 24 C    | |
  | | Wind 18 km/h       Rain 10%       Hum 56%  | |
  | '--------------------------------------------' |
  |                                                |
  | [ Overview ] [ Wind ] [ Rain ] [ Humidity ]    |
  |                                                |
  | .--------------- selected metric ------------. |
  | | Rain by hour                               | |
  | |                                            | |
  | |  45%          x                            | |
  | |  30%       x  |  x                         | |
  | |  15%    x  |  |  |  x  x                   | |
  | |   0%  x |  |  |  |  |  |                   | |
  | |      Now 14 15 16 17 18                   | |
  | |                                            | |
  | | Now 5%  14:00 8%  15:00 42%  16:00 20%   | |
  | '--------------------------------------------' |
  |                                                |
  | .------------------ details ----------------.  |
  | | Current hour                               |  |
  | | Temperature 23 C     Wind 8 km/h           |  |
  | | Precip 5%           Humidity 56%           |  |
  | '--------------------------------------------' |
  |                                                |
  | 7-day forecast                                 |
  | Today     sun            24 C / 15 C           |
  |                                                |
  | HOME        MAP        ALERTS      Settings    |
  '------------------------------------------------'

Layout notes
- Keep the hero compact and put the dashboard behavior into tabs.
- Tabs: Overview, Wind, Rain, Humidity.
- Overview shows the familiar current conditions and small hourly cards.
- Wind tab shows a wind-speed trend and optional direction markers.
- Rain tab shows precipitation probability by hour.
- Humidity tab shows humidity by hour.
- Each tab has the same panel size, which prevents layout jumps.

Interaction notes
- Segmented tabs switch the selected metric.
- The selected metric panel can be a simple bar/line chart in the first version.
- Tap/drag over the chart to select an hour.
- Details panel below always shows full data for the selected hour.

Implementation direction
- Add DashboardMetric enum: overview, wind, rain, humidity.
- Build a HomeMetricTabs widget that mirrors map layer chip styling.
- Add HourlyMetricChart for the selected metric.
- Add SelectedHourDetails using the same four values:
  temperature, wind, precipitation, humidity.
- This design has the most future capacity for pressure, visibility, air quality, and dew point.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Recommendation
Use Design 1 for the first implementation.

Reasons
- It answers the user need directly: every visible hourly card can show wind,
  precipitation, and humidity.
- It requires the smallest visual and navigation change.
- It keeps the current dashboard rhythm and bottom navigation untouched.
- The data model change is straightforward because OpenWeather hourly data already carries
  pop, humidity, wind_speed, and wind_deg.

Suggested implementation sequence
1. Extend HourlyForecast with windSpeed, windDirection, pop, and humidity.
2. Parse those fields in HourlyForecast.fromJson.
3. Replace the current hourly strip cards with detail cards from Design 1.
4. Add an optional metric filter after the richer hourly cards are stable.
5. Consider Design 2 or 3 later if users need comparison or deeper weather tooling.
